rComments: I took Confucian Philosophy with her in second year and I never regretted it. The follow up Confucius Ethics and Morality that she teaches outlines the cosmological view of both ancient and modern Chinese family dynamics and thought. Prof. Yan is a prof that earns your respect and esteem and isn't afraid to elaborate or speak slower if asked.

Prof Yan was one of the greatest teachers I have ever had. If teaching is an art, then she would have the simplicity of Monet, the mastery of Rembrandt, and the risque style of Picasso all united with a humble approach to philosophy, that creates a wonderfully unique experience. Simply the best!

Professor Yan is one the greatest assets of the University of Toronto's Philosophy Dept. She exemplifies a brilliant grasp of Chinese Philosophy combined with an unparalleled teaching style that ensures that students always get the most out of her lectures. A pleasure to have had as an instructor!!!
